questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a `HashSet` fails to remove an element. The application uses a Spring `@Service` to manage `UserSession` objects. Snippet:

java
@Transactional
public void expireSession(Set<UserSession> sessions, Long sessionId) {
    sessions.stream()
            .filter(s -> s.getId().equals(sessionId))
            .findFirst()
            .ifPresent(session -> {
                session.setExpiryTime(Instant.now()); // expiryTime is used in hashCode()
                boolean removed = sessions.remove(session);
                log.info("Removed: {}", removed);
            });
}

In logs, `removed` is consistently `false` even though the session exists in the set.
